div.h2: From Hardware Signal to Process Resumption

g.title: CPU checks for pending interrupts after each instruction completes

ol.li: Save ALL registers - missing one corrupts state
Send EOI - or PIC freezes forever
Keep handler fast - interrupts disabled during handler
Don't block - no sleeping in interrupt context

div.p: SS (if CPL change) ESP (if CPL change) EFLAGS always CS always EIP always Error (some exceptions)
asm pusha ; eax,ecx,edx,ebx,esp,ebp,esi,edi push ds, es, fs, gs mov ax, 0x10 ; kernel DS mov ds, ax mov es, ax

g.title: Pass register state pointer to C handler

div.p: ESP [ptr to state] C argument [gs] our push [fs] [es] [ds] [edi] pusha [esi] [ebp] [esp] (old) [ebx] [edx] [ecx] [eax] [int_no] our push [err_code] our push [EIP] CPU push [CS] CPU push [EFLAGS] CPU push [ESP] (user) CPU (if ring3ring0) [SS] (user) CPU (if ring3ring0)
asm pop gs, fs, es, ds popa ; restore all GPRs add esp, 8 ; skip int_no, err_code iret ; return from interrupt

g.title: Pops: EIP, CS, EFLAGS And if returning to ring 3: ESP, SS

div.p: All registers restored to exact pre-interrupt state. Process continues as if nothing happened.
